Solution: This is a finite geometric series with first term $\frac{1}{3}$, common ratio $\frac{1}{3}$ and $6$ terms. Therefore the sum is: $$\frac{\frac{1}{3}\left(1-\frac{1}{3^{6}}\right)}{1-\frac{1}{3}}
=\frac{\frac{3^{6}-1}{3^{7}}}{\frac{2}{3}}
= \frac{3^{6}-1}{2\cdot3^{6}}=\frac{729-1}{2\cdot 729} = \boxed{\frac{364}{729}}.$$

