Solution: We first note that $\sqrt{3}\times 3^{\frac{1}{2}} = 3^{\frac{1}{2}}\times 3^{\frac{1}{2}} = 3^{\frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{2}} = 3^1 = 3$ and $4^{3/2} = (2^2)^{\frac{3}{2}} = 2^{2\cdot \frac{3}{2}} = 2^3 = 8$, so \begin{align*}
