Solution: In the coordinate plane, let $A = (0,1),$ $B = (1,-1),$ and $P = (x,x).$  Then
\[AP = \sqrt{x^2 + (1 - x)^2}\]and
\[BP = \sqrt{(x - 1)^2 + (x + 1)^2},\]so we want to minimize $AP + BP,$ subject to $P$ lying on the line $y = x.$

[asy]
unitsize(2.5 cm);

pair A, B, P;

A = (0,1);
B = (1,-1);
P = (0.8,0.8);

