Solution: Plotting $y = |x - 3|$ and $y = 4 - |x - 1|,$ we find that the two graphs intersect at $(0,3)$ and $(4,1).$


[asy]
unitsize(1 cm);

real funcone (real x) {
  return(abs(x - 3));
}

real functwo (real x) {
  return(4 - abs(x - 1));
}

fill((3,0)--(4,1)--(1,4)--(0,3)--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw(graph(funcone,-0.5,4.5));
draw(graph(functwo,-0.5,4.5));
