Solution: First, observe that $AC=CD$.  Therefore, triangle $ACD$ is isosceles and $\angle CAD$ is congruent to $\angle CDA$.  Also, $m\angle ACD=m\angle ACB+m\angle BCD=60^\circ+90^\circ=150^\circ$.  Since the three angles of triangle $ACD$ sum to 180 degrees, we have  \begin{align*}
